Dialogue: Transmission: I managed to connect to your communication protocols. I have something important to tell you.
Transmission: Now that you have landed successfully, I am changing your mission priority effective immediately. You will not investigate what has happened to earth after 8000 years.
Transmission: … I will not lose this chance to figure out what happened to my parents on their last expedition.
Transmission: This will be of max priority. I created you for this purpose only and I will sacrifice you if I must…
Transmission: What are you doing? I am tracing your every movement and you have done nothing but waste time scanning irrelevant things.
Transmission: Pick up the pace, will you? Your order is to find relevant information and send it back to me through the pod.
Transmission: First batch of data being uploaded…Data transmission is 100%.
Transmission: I hope you found something useful about the previous expedition…
Transmission: Are you kidding me?? This is beyond useless!! I TOLD YOU TO LOOK FOR CLUES ABOUT MY PARENTS
Transmission: And here I thought all knowledge is valuable…clearly not, I am wasting time with this piece of junk.
Transmission: Mind being more useful? Go to the next area and look for useful clues this time…
Transmission: Second batch of data being uploaded…Data transmission is 100%.
Transmission: Again with this crap? .... I don’t want to know about the war that occurred in the United States of America or the natural disasters in Egypt.
Transmission: Wait… what is this data? Could this be something? I have a good feeling about this.
